column5: It's labeled Storm on the lip and I'm pretty sure it's a thunderstick or thunderstick jr. but was looking for confirmation. It's different from the model available now but I seem to remember that they changed it at some point.  It's about 4.5 inches long.
It looks like a knock off of a floating Rapala?
It was good enough that when rapala bought storm they changed it. It's plastic, not balsa and has a single large ball bearing rattle.
You have it right Rob. Thunder stick. I remember when they came out. They looked cheap IMO. I stuck with buy husky jerks.
It's exactly what you think it is.
